<section>
  <p>
    I'm a computer architect interested in both human and silicon computers. I enjoy
    the struggle of turning ideas into products with impact.
  </p>
  <p>
    I'm a professor in the Department of Computer Science and Engineering at the
    University of Michigan and a co-founder of
    Replicam, a company building the most accurate models of the
    human brain. I've co-authored over 80 publications and received various best
    paper awards, including the 2017 ISCA Influential Paper Award for groundbreaking
    research in power-efficient computing, and the 2021 MICRO Test of Time award.
  </p>
  <p>
    I was responsible for product strategy in Cisco's Emerging Technology &amp;
    Incubation Group, following my tenure as CEO of Banzai Cloud,
    a startup Cisco acquired that turned cloud-native dreams into enterprise reality
    through cloud software. Previously, I served as general manager of the Internet
    of Things business unit and as VP of research and development at Arm.
    I received a PhD in computer science and engineering, as well as several other
    degrees, from the University of Michigan.
  </p>
  <p>
    You can reach me at <a href="mailto:{{ site.email }}">{{ site.email }}</a>.
  </p>
